# Private package resolution for @syncsalez-dev/* — sync-core and
# sync-rn live on GitHub Packages, not the public npm registry.
#
# Auth lives in your USER-level ~/.npmrc, not here. Add this line
# to ~/.npmrc (Windows path: C:\Users\<you>\.npmrc) with a GitHub
# PAT that has `read:packages` scope:
#
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=ghp_yourLiteralTokenHere
#
# The literal token is fine in ~/.npmrc since that file isn't
# committed anywhere. This project-level .npmrc only handles the
# scope→registry mapping — no auth — so it can stay tracked.

@syncsalez-dev:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}